snippet.textDisplay:
Comments like that really just show how ignorant people are about what gaining weight is actually like. I don’t speak for everyone but I’ve been really struggling with it the past year when I started binge eating and got depressed. Along with a lot of other things in my life, my weight gain causes me so much stress and anxiety. And being alone and stressed made me turn to food for comfort even more. It also made me stop my healthy habits like going to gym because I had so much anxiety about people who’ve seen me before seeing me again. But then I would get anxiety about how I wasn’t exercising. Almost every single day I’d cry and break down about it. I don’t think people could truly understand how mentally challenging weight gain can be. I know I didn’t until I went through it. And I’m still in it. There isn’t a day when I look at myself and am not disgusted. Every time I go into public or have to meet someone I get anxious and I feel like everyone is looking at me and noticing how overweight and ugly I am. I’m convinced no one would ever date me or could ever even look at me like that unless I lose the weight. And I try my very best to avoid any interactions with people I knew or knew me before I gained weight. I need to go to the dentist but I’m scared of them judging me. Family gatherings freak me out. I avoid certain grocery stores because I might see an old classmate there. And even with friends and my close family, i never try to mention weight, food or exercising. When it comes up I get so anxious and I divert the conversation. Sometimes I wish I could talk about how I actually feel about it but I just can’t bring myself to, so I just avoid it. I’m already constantly paranoid about them thinking about it. I can’t imagine how it must be for Shane where he has to present himself to millions and millions of people... i don’t know if I could ever cope with the anxiety that would give me.
Sorry for that super long rant if anyone even read it lol. If you did and you’re going through something similar just know you’re not alone <3
